    "ML methods can also be classified according to the availability of labeled data in supervised and unsupervised learning.",
    "Supervised learning uses labeled/classified data.",
    "This indicates that each data point x has a specific outcome y. Unsupervised ML models use algorithms to detect similar patterns in the data.",
    "Classification and regression are two types of supervised learning, with linear and nonlinear methods/algorithms as shown in Fig. 6.",
    "Classification algorithmsClassification is a supervised learning algorithm."
